PLDT Communications to Transfer Manila Electric Shares to Beacon

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-10-20T00:51:30Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-20/pldt-communications-to-transfer-manila-electric-shares-to-beacon.html
Metro Pacific Investments Corp. (MPI)  said
a special purpose company it jointly owns with  PLDT
Communications and Energy Ventures Inc. (PCEV)  will acquire 68.8
million  Manila Electric Co. (MER)  shares from PLDT Communications at
220 pesos each or 15.136 billion pesos.  PLDT Communications will then subscribe to 1.199 billion
preferred shares of the special purpose company, Beacon Electric
Asset Holdings Inc., for 15.136 billion pesos, Metro Pacific
said in a disclosure to the stock exchange today.  The acquisition of the shares will bring Beacon’s interest
in Meralco, the nation’s biggest power distribution utility, to
45.35 percent, Metro Pacific said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cecilia Yap at 
 cyap19@bloomberg.net  